page.title: 09HOUSING
page.content: The Old Buckenham area consists of semi-detached, detached and farm houses. Round the Green the houses are mainly detached and semi-detached; cottages and bungalows, as well as farmhouses, are dotted around the outskirts. The approximate population is 915. There are two main residential areas. Some people live around the Green, which is like a big playing field. There is a private estate called Oaklands and a Council estate called St. Andrews Close. In Fen Street there are a lot of farmhouses as well as cottages, semi-detached and detached houses and bungalows. In all, there are 58 semi-detached, 11 farm houses, 28 cottages, 76 detached houses and 41 bungalows. Types of farming in the area include fruit growing, dairy and arable.
